Padraic's ever been," he said.

934
01:10:33,650 --> 01:10:35,320
"I think I like him again now."

935
01:10:40,440 --> 01:10:41,310
Aye.

936
01:10:43,446 --> 01:10:47,286
Maybe this whole thing has just been
about gettin' you to try a new tack,

937
01:10:47,320 --> 01:10:49,780
start standin' up for yourself a bit.

938
01:10:49,800 --> 01:10:51,100
Do you think?

939
01:10:51,280 --> 01:10:53,580
Yeah, and be less of a, you know,

940
01:10:53,760 --> 01:10:56,053
whiny little dull-arse.

941
01:10:57,126 --> 01:10:59,313
Well, I have been less of a whiny
little dull-arse, actually.

942
01:10:59,330 --> 01:11:00,550
Have ya, yeah?

943
01:11:00,720 --> 01:11:02,693
Just yesterday, there was this musician fella

944
01:11:02,720 --> 01:11:04,620
that Colm was getting along great with.

945
01:11:04,640 --> 01:11:05,640
And what did I do?

946
01:11:05,810 --> 01:11:07,526
I went and sent him
packing from the island.

947
01:11:07,550 --> 01:11:09,340
Did ya? How?

948
01:11:09,510 --> 01:11:11,526
I told him a bread van
crashed into his daddy,

949
01:11:11,600 --> 01:11:14,400
and he'd have to be rushing
home to him, lest he die.

950
01:11:17,430 --> 01:11:18,430
Oh...

951
01:11:21,870 --> 01:11:24,560
That sounds like the meanest
thing I've ever heard.

952
01:11:24,700 --> 01:11:26,790
Huh?

953
01:11:26,970 --> 01:11:30,360
Well, aye, it was a bit mean, but...

954
01:11:32,140 --> 01:11:33,800
he'll be fine once he gets home

955
01:11:33,846 --> 01:11:36,500
and he finds his daddy hasn't
been hit by a bread van.

956
01:11:38,500 --> 01:11:41,173
I used to think you were the nicest of them.

957
01:11:42,500 --> 01:11:43,840
