958
01:11:43,850 --> 01:11:45,460
I am the nicest of them.

959
01:11:48,730 --> 01:11:49,550
Ar, Dominic, now!

960
01:11:52,640 --> 01:11:54,640
Well, maybe I'm not a happy lad, so!

961
01:11:56,780 --> 01:11:58,300
Maybe this is the new me!

962
01:12:00,560 --> 01:12:01,560
Aye.

963
01:12:03,130 --> 01:12:04,650
Maybe this is the new me.

964
01:12:39,430 --> 01:12:40,430
Howdo!

965
01:12:40,600 --> 01:12:42,340
Jesus Christ, Dominic!

966
01:12:42,520 --> 01:12:44,626
Would you ever stop creeping up on people?

967
01:12:44,690 --> 01:12:46,633
You almost gave me a fecking heart attack!

968
01:12:46,700 --> 01:12:47,806
I wasn't creeping up on ya.

969
01:12:47,870 --> 01:12:49,026
I was sidling up on ya.

970
01:12:49,050 --> 01:12:51,050
Between you and that ghoul, Jesus!

971
01:12:51,220 --> 01:12:53,920
I always call her a ghoul, too,
because she is a ghoul.

972
01:12:54,100 --> 01:12:56,580
Jeez, we have a lot in common, don't we?
Me and you.

973
01:12:56,750 --> 01:12:58,710
Calling old people ghouls and that.

974
01:13:02,580 --> 01:13:04,450
It's a great old lake, isn't it?

975
01:13:09,680 --> 01:13:11,720
I'm glad I caught you, actually.

976
01:13:11,900 --> 01:13:14,666
Because there was somethin' I was
wantin' to ask ya, actually.

977
01:13:14,720 --> 01:13:17,600
And discovering how much
we have in common,

978
01:13:17,770 --> 01:13:20,430
well, it just makes me
want to ask you even more.

979
01:13:20,600 --> 01:13:21,866
We don't have anything in common.

980
01:13:21,910 --> 01:13:24,300
