1024
01:16:09,940 --> 01:16:11,680
I haven't finished with your slagging.

1025
01:16:11,860 --> 01:16:13,990
We were doin' so well, Padraic.

1026
01:16:14,170 --> 01:16:15,690
I wasn't doing so well.

1027
01:16:18,210 --> 01:16:20,210
I was doing terrible.

1028
01:16:20,390 --> 01:16:22,220
All right, I was doin' so well.

1029
01:16:22,390 --> 01:16:24,350
Yeah, well, it can't all be
you, you, you, can it?

1030
01:16:24,520 --> 01:16:26,090
Yes, it can.

1031
01:16:26,260 --> 01:16:28,050
There's two of us in this. No, there isn't.

1032
01:16:28,220 --> 01:16:29,440
It takes two to tango.

1033
01:16:29,620 --> 01:16:31,140
I don't want to tango.

1034
01:16:31,310 --> 01:16:33,140
Well, you danced with your dog.

1035
01:16:45,370 --> 01:16:48,550
Talkin' of tangos, how's
your new tune comin' along?

1036
01:16:48,720 --> 01:16:50,680
I just finished it, actually.

1037
01:16:51,590 --> 01:16:53,353
Just this morning.

1038
01:16:53,860 --> 01:16:55,600
No, Colm, that's great, like!

1039
01:16:55,770 --> 01:16:57,730
That's why I was dancing with me dog.

1040
01:16:59,040 --> 01:17:00,950
I don't usually dance with me dog.

1041
01:17:01,120 --> 01:17:04,000
There's no harm dancin' with your dog.

1042
01:17:04,170 --> 01:17:07,000
I'd dance with me donkey
if I knew how. And she did.

1043
01:17:09,570 --> 01:17:10,790
Is it good?

1044
01:17:10,960 --> 01:17:11,870
Your tune?

1045
01:17:16,180 --> 01:17:18,930
Mm, what's it called?

1046
01:17:19,100 --> 01:17:21,670
"The Banshees of Inisherin,"
I was thinking.

1047
01:17:24,450 --> 01:17:26,890
But there are no banshees on Inisherin.

1048
01:17:27,060 --> 01:17:30,126
I know, I just like
the double S-H sounds.

1049
01:17:30,760 --> 01:17:32,330
Aye.

1050
01:17:32,500 --> 01:17:34,900
There's plenty of double S-H on Inisherin.

1051
01:17:35,070 --> 01:17:35,990
Yeah.

1052
01:17:36,160 --> 01:17:39,340
Maybe there are banshees, too.

1053
01:17:39,510 --> 01:17:43,210
I just don't think that they
scream to portend death anymore.

1054
01:17:43,380 --> 01:17:47,690
I think they just sit back, amused, and observe.

1055
01:17:48,740 --> 01:17:49,650
Portend?

1056
01:17:50,740 --> 01:17:51,740
Yeah.

1057
01:17:55,033 --> 01:17:57,946
I keep having thoughts about
playing it for you at your funeral.

1058
01:17:57,960 --> 01:18:00,140
But that wouldn't be fair
on either of us, would it?

1059
01:18:14,070 --> 01:18:17,110
Well, that's great that you
finished your tune, Colm.

1060
01:18:17,290 --> 01:18:19,073
That's more than great.

1061
01:18:19,550 --> 01:18:20,290
That's...

1062
01:18:21,940 --> 01:18:22,900
really great.

1063
01:18:34,520 --> 01:18:37,530
So, do you want to meet me down the pub, Colm?

1064
01:18:38,870 --> 01:18:41,113
We could celebrate your tune, like.

1065
01:18:47,540 --> 01:18:49,710
Only if you'd like, like.

1066
01:18:49,890 --> 01:18:52,630
But I could run up ahead.
Order them in.

1067
01:18:56,070 --> 01:18:58,146
Why don't you do that, Padraic?

1068
01:18:59,900 --> 01:19:01,030
Why don't I run up...

1069
01:19:03,380 --> 01:19:04,250
and order them?

1070
01:19:06,340 --> 01:19:07,160
Well, I will so.

1071
01:19:10,910 --> 01:19:13,080
Jeez, that went well!
And maybe on the way,

1072
01:19:13,126 --> 01:19:15,446
I can find that student friend
of yours, that Declan fella!

1073
01:19:15,480 --> 01:19:17,253
I told him his daddy was dying,
so he'd feck off home

1074
01:19:17,260 --> 01:19:19,830
and leave us alone,
but there's no need now!

1075
01:19:20,000 --> 01:19:21,220
Sure he could join us.

1076
01:20:14,220 --> 01:20:16,580
What are you sitting over there
for when I'm over here?

1077
01:20:16,580 --> 01:20:19,173
Just thought I'd have a sit
for meself, you know.

1078
01:20:19,930 --> 01:20:21,240
Wait for me friend.

1079
01:20:21,410 --> 01:20:23,370
Are you fecking joking me?

1080
01:20:23,540 --> 01:20:25,070
Your four-fingered friend?

1081
01:20:25,200 --> 01:20:26,660
I mean, are you fecking joking me?

1082
01:20:26,680 --> 01:20:28,900
No, I'm not fecking joking ya.

1083
01:20:29,070 --> 01:20:31,820
He just needed a bit of tough love was all.

1084
01:21:05,760 --> 01:21:07,240
Siobhan, do you want a sherry?

1085
01:21:07,410 --> 01:21:08,630
No.Righty-ho.

1086
01:21:10,900 --> 01:21:11,900
What are you doin'?

1087
01:21:12,070 --> 01:21:13,200
Me? Yes, you.

1088
01:21:13,380 --> 01:21:15,160
Nothing. Just drinkin'.

1089
01:21:15,340 --> 01:21:17,160
Not waitin'?Not waitin'.

1090
01:21:17,193 --> 01:21:18,893
Well, he is waitin', Siobhan.
He's waitin' for Colm Doherty.

1091
01:21:18,900 --> 01:21:19,820
I amn't waitin'.

1092
01:21:19,900 --> 01:21:21,093
He just told me he was waitin'.

1093
01:21:21,120 --> 01:21:22,520
Telltale!

1094
01:21:25,610 --> 01:21:29,780
Come home with me, Padraic.
I've somethin' to discuss with ya.

1095
01:21:30,090 --> 01:21:32,153
You've somethin' to discuss with me?

1096
01:21:32,790 --> 01:21:34,530
That sounds, uh...

1097
01:21:34,700 --> 01:21:36,790
I don't want to discuss somethin'.

1098
01:21:37,100 --> 01:21:39,490
Well, ya have to, 'cause I'm leavin'.

1099
01:21:41,140 --> 01:21:41,970
Leavin'?

1100
01:21:45,320 --> 01:21:46,280
Like leavin'?

1101
01:21:48,370 --> 01:21:49,060
Like...

1102
01:21:51,150 --> 01:21:51,890
not staying?

1103
01:21:56,420 --> 01:21:57,420
Yeah.

1104
01:22:41,380 --> 01:22:42,510
But what about me?

1105
01:22:42,810 --> 01:22:44,030
What about you?

1106
01:22:44,210 --> 01:22:45,620
I'll have no friends at all left!

1107
01:22:45,640 --> 01:22:47,730
You'll have Dominic. Ah here!

1108
01:22:47,910 --> 01:22:50,130
And he's gone off me now, too.

1109
01:22:50,200 --> 01:22:53,146
What kind of a place is it when
the village gom goes off ya?

1110
01:22:53,170 --> 01:22:55,090
And who's gonna do the cookin'?

1111
01:22:55,260 --> 01:22:57,513
Oh, that's your first question, isn't it?
"Who's gonna do the cookin'?"

1112
01:22:57,570 --> 01:22:59,306
Well, it wasn't me first question, was it?

1113
01:22:59,350 --> 01:23:01,940
"But what about me?" was me first question.

1114
01:23:36,390 --> 01:23:37,300
Padraic.

1115
01:23:39,220 --> 01:23:40,350
Padraic!

1116
01:23:44,350 --> 01:23:47,310
Now?
But you can't be leavin' now!

1117
01:23:47,490 --> 01:23:49,530
I can be leavin' now.

1118
01:23:49,566 --> 01:23:52,240
I can't be waitin' round
for any more of this madness!

1119
01:23:52,270 --> 01:23:54,490
What the hell did you say to him, Padraic?

1120
01:23:54,670 --> 01:23:55,630
Nothin' really.

1121
01:23:56,980 --> 01:24:00,206
Well, I'd sort of had a chat
with Dominic earlier.

1122
01:24:00,590 --> 01:24:02,760
And a new sort of,

1123
01:24:02,940 --> 01:24:06,020
you know, standin' up for meself
sort of tack we thought I should try.

1124
01:24:06,030 --> 01:24:07,420
God!

1125
01:24:07,453 --> 01:24:11,073
It was all going fine until he
chopped off all his fingers.

1126
01:24:18,780 --> 01:24:20,480
Me books wouldn't fit.

1127
01:24:21,910 --> 01:24:24,000
Would you look after them for me?

1128
01:24:24,180 --> 01:24:25,870
Ar, don't go, Siobhan.

1129
01:24:26,050 --> 01:24:27,610
They're all I have, really.

1130
01:24:29,830 --> 01:24:31,440
Apart from the obvious.

1131
01:24:39,320 --> 01:24:41,320
You'll be back soon, won't you, Siobhan?

1132
01:24:42,410 --> 01:24:44,890
Oh, Padraic!

1133
01:24:45,070 --> 01:24:46,590
Don't say, "Oh, Padraic."

1134
01:24:47,500 --> 01:24:48,980
Say yes.

1135
01:28:06,350 --> 01:28:07,400
Ah, Jenny.

1136
01:28:47,660 --> 01:28:48,350
Oh.

1137
01:30:52,870 --> 01:30:54,220
I don't want to talk.

1138
01:30:55,390 --> 01:30:57,220
Don't go killin' his dog now.

1139
01:30:57,400 --> 01:30:58,560
And don't be puttin' things in me head

1140
01:30:58,610 --> 01:31:00,140
that weren't there in the first feckin' place,

1141
01:31:00,166 --> 01:31:01,533
you feckin' nutbag!

1142
01:31:02,360 --> 01:31:03,790
"Nutbag!"

1143
01:31:57,320 --> 01:31:59,446
What would I ever hurt you for?

1144
01:32:00,940 --> 01:32:03,293
You're the only nice thing about him.

1145
01:32:32,666 --> 01:32:35,353
How are you, Padraic?
You're lookin' well.

1146
01:32:42,380 --> 01:32:44,800
That's lovely, lads.

1147
01:32:49,160 --> 01:32:51,400
I don't need your apologies, all right?

1148
01:32:51,730 --> 01:32:53,420
It's a relief to me.

1149
01:32:53,600 --> 01:32:55,170
So, let's just call it quits

1150
01:32:55,340 --> 01:32:58,720
and agree to go our separate ways,
for good this time.

1151
01:33:01,000 --> 01:33:03,740
Your fat fingers killed me little donkey today.

1152
01:33:03,910 --> 01:33:06,790
So, no, we won't call it quits.

1153
01:33:06,960 --> 01:33:08,540
We'll call it the start.

1154
01:33:09,180 --> 01:33:10,620
You're jokin' me.Yeah, no.

1155
01:33:10,790 --> 01:33:12,570
I'm not jokin' ya.

1156
01:33:12,750 --> 01:33:14,580
So tomorrow, Sunday,

1157
01:33:14,750 --> 01:33:17,140
God's day, around 2:00,

1158
01:33:17,320 --> 01:33:19,560
I'm going to call up to your house
and I'm gonna set fire to it,

1159
01:33:19,580 --> 01:33:21,793
and hopefully you'll still be inside it.

1160
01:33:22,840 --> 01:33:25,286
But I won't be checkin' either way.

1161
01:33:27,590 --> 01:33:30,053
Just be sure and leave your dog outside.

1162
01:33:30,640 --> 01:33:32,290
I've nothing against that gom.

1163
01:33:34,860 --> 01:33:37,380
Or you can do whatever's
in your power to stop me.

1164
01:33:41,120 --> 01:33:42,860
To our graves we're taking this.

1165
01:33:44,820 --> 01:33:46,753
To one of our graves, anyways.

1166
01:33:48,570 --> 01:33:49,780
Here.

1167
01:33:49,960 --> 01:33:51,920
I've a bone to pick with you, dreary.

1168
01:33:52,090 --> 01:33:53,906
Is that little gobshite
of mine at your place again?

1169
01:33:53,920 --> 01:33:56,080
Leave him, Peadar.
His donkey's just died.

1170
01:33:56,100 --> 01:33:57,490
Did he?

1171
01:33:57,660 --> 01:33:59,190
The little miniature fella?

1172
01:33:59,360 --> 01:34:01,410
Well, Jesus, boys,
I'll tell ya this much...

1173
01:34:13,900 --> 01:34:14,720
Two o'clock.

1174
01:35:16,650 --> 01:35:18,090
I killed a miniature donkey.

1175
01:35:22,220 --> 01:35:23,790
It was by accident...

1176
01:35:27,360 --> 01:35:28,620
but I do feel bad about it.

1177
01:35:31,890 --> 01:35:35,460
Do you think God gives a damn
about miniature donkeys, Colm?

1178
01:35:37,810 --> 01:35:38,810
I fear he doesn't.

1179
01:35:42,070 --> 01:35:44,200
And I fear that's where
it's all gone wrong.

1180
01:35:47,030 --> 01:35:47,770
Is that it?

1181
01:35:49,120 --> 01:35:51,080
Is what it?

1182
01:35:51,250 --> 01:35:53,540
Aren't you forgetting a couple of things?

1183
01:35:54,520 --> 01:35:57,260
No, I think I've covered it.

1184
01:35:57,430 --> 01:36:00,520
Wouldn't you say punching a policeman is a sin?

1185
01:36:01,870 --> 01:36:03,570
Ah here.

1186
01:36:03,740 --> 01:36:05,700
If punching a policeman is a sin,

1187
01:36:05,880 --> 01:36:08,580
we may as well just pack up and go home.

1188
01:36:10,530 --> 01:36:12,490
And self-mutilation is a sin.

1189
01:36:13,750 --> 01:36:15,593
It's one of the biggest.

1190
01:36:15,890 --> 01:36:17,190
Is it?

1191
01:36:17,370 --> 01:36:20,240
Self-mutilation, so you have me there.

1192
01:36:20,410 --> 01:36:21,590
Multiplied by five.

1193
01:36:27,330 --> 01:36:28,860
How's the despair?

1194
01:36:33,730 --> 01:36:34,780
It's back a bit.

1195
01:36:38,040 --> 01:36:40,500
But you're not gonna
do anything about it?

1196
01:36:44,310 --> 01:36:46,400
I'm not gonna
do anything about it, no.

1197
01:37:01,320 --> 01:37:03,500
Dear Padraic,

1198
01:37:03,670 --> 01:37:07,720
I am safely ensconced in the mainland
and, Padraic, it's lovely here.

1199
01:37:08,030 --> 01:37:10,526
There's a river running
past my window as I write,

1200
01:37:10,550 --> 01:37:13,510
and the people already seem
less bitter and mental.

1201
01:37:13,680 --> 01:37:17,950
I'm not sure why, but I think it's
'cause a lot of them are from Spain.

1202
01:37:18,120 --> 01:37:21,650
Mostly, I wanted to say there's a
spare bed here for you, Padraic.

1203
01:37:21,820 --> 01:37:25,390
And with the war almost over, I
think there'd be work for ya here.

1204
01:37:25,570 --> 01:37:28,000
Because there's nothing
for you on Inisherin.

1205
01:37:28,180 --> 01:37:30,530
Nothing but more bleakness and grudges

1206
01:37:30,700 --> 01:37:33,360
and loneliness and spite

1207
01:37:33,530 --> 01:37:36,360
and the slow passing of time until death.

1208
01:37:36,530 --> 01:37:38,840
And sure, you can do that anywhere.

1209
01:37:41,230 --> 01:37:44,370
So come, Padraic. Leave there.

1210
01:37:44,540 --> 01:37:47,393
Dominic can look after Jenny
and the rest of your animals.

1211
01:37:47,410 --> 01:37:50,000
They could move into the house together.

1212
01:37:59,250 --> 01:37:59,950
Hut!

1213
01:38:22,100 --> 01:38:24,760
So come now, Padraic, please.

1214
01:38:28,760 --> 01:38:30,720
Before it's all too late.

1215
01:41:21,850 --> 01:41:23,540
Dear Siobhan.

1216
01:41:23,720 --> 01:41:26,940
Obviously, I don't know
what "ensconced" is,

1217
01:41:27,110 --> 01:41:30,290
but I thank you for the offer
of the free bed and the whatnot.

1218
01:41:30,460 --> 01:41:33,273
But I won't be takin' you up
on it, I'm afraid.

1219
01:41:34,340 --> 01:41:36,860
As I told you, me life is on Inisherin.

1220
01:41:37,030 --> 01:41:38,690
Me friends, me animals.

1221
01:41:42,820 --> 01:41:44,300
Even now as I write,

1222
01:41:44,480 --> 01:41:46,506
little donkey Jenny
is looking at me, saying,

1223
01:41:46,520 --> 01:41:48,960
"Please don't go, Padraic.
We'd miss ya."

1224
01:41:49,260 --> 01:41:51,310
And nuzzling me, the gilly-gooly.

1225
01:41:52,400 --> 01:41:53,490
Get off, Jenny.

1226
01:41:57,230 --> 01:41:58,980
MRS. McCORMICK: Psst!

1227
01:42:08,200 --> 01:42:09,680
In other news,

1228
01:42:09,980 --> 01:42:12,500
in sadder news, actually,

1229
01:42:12,680 --> 01:42:15,553
I won't be able to ask Dominic
anything, I'm afraid.

1230
01:42:17,500 --> 01:42:20,826
Because they found him
in the lake this morning.

1231
01:42:24,470 --> 01:42:26,910
I suppose he must've slipped and fell in.

1232
01:42:35,053 --> 01:42:37,920
So, there'd be no one to take
care of the animals, anyway.

1233
01:43:01,640 --> 01:43:03,160
No other news, really.

1234
01:43:12,650 --> 01:43:14,390
Except that I love you, Siobhan.

1235
01:43:15,570 --> 01:43:16,740
And I miss ya.

1236
01:43:19,530 --> 01:43:21,440
And I hope I'll see ya again someday.

1237
01:43:24,450 --> 01:43:25,800
If you ever come back home.

1238
01:43:28,750 --> 01:43:30,840
Come back home, Siobhan.

1239
01:43:36,240 --> 01:43:38,850
Yours sincerely, your loving brother...

1240
01:43:41,290 --> 01:43:42,550
Padraic Suilleabhain.

1241
01:45:16,910 --> 01:45:18,600
Suppose me house makes us quits.

1242
01:45:20,820 --> 01:45:23,780
If you'd stayed in your house,
that would've made us quits.

1243
01:45:23,960 --> 01:45:26,090
But you didn't, did ya,
so it doesn't, does it?

1244
01:45:38,190 --> 01:45:40,230
I'm sorry about your donkey, Padraic.

1245
01:45:40,930 --> 01:45:42,020
Honestly, I am.

1246
01:45:44,930 --> 01:45:46,410
I don't fucking care.

1247
01:46:02,766 --> 01:46:06,020
Haven't heard any rifle fire from
the mainland in a day or two.

1248
01:46:06,040 --> 01:46:08,740
I think they're coming to the end of it.

1249
01:46:08,910 --> 01:46:11,740
I'm sure they'll be at it again
soon enough, aren't you?

1250
01:46:13,960 --> 01:46:15,790
Some things there's no movin' on from.

1251
01:46:19,270 --> 01:46:21,620
And I think that's a good thing.

1252
01:46:43,640 --> 01:46:44,520
Padraic.

1253
01:46:50,960 --> 01:46:53,873
Thanks for lookin' after me dog
for me, anyways.

1254
01:46:59,700 --> 01:47:00,570
Any time.
